description.p:
Individual densities are calculated by: ρx=m⁢1⁢x⁢ρ0m⁢1-m⁢2
wherein
px = is the density of the sample, in g per ml;
m1 = is the mass of the sample in position 1 an air, in g;
m2 = is the mass of the sample in position 2 in the buoyancy medium, in g; and
ρ0 = is the density of the buoyancy medium, in g per ml, at the respective measuring temperature.
